018package org.apache.hadoop.hbase.rest.model;
019
020import static org.junit.Assert.assertEquals;
021
022import org.apache.hadoop.hbase.HBaseClassTestRule;
023import org.apache.hadoop.hbase.testclassification.RestTests;
024import org.apache.hadoop.hbase.testclassification.SmallTests;
025import org.junit.ClassRule;
026import org.junit.experimental.categories.Category;
027
028@Category({ RestTests.class, SmallTests.class })
029public class TestVersionModel extends TestModelBase<VersionModel> {
030
031  @ClassRule
032  public static final HBaseClassTestRule CLASS_RULE =
033    HBaseClassTestRule.forClass(TestVersionModel.class);
034
035  private static final String REST_VERSION = "0.0.1";
036  private static final String OS_VERSION = "Linux 2.6.18-128.1.6.el5.centos.plusxen amd64";
037  private static final String JVM_VERSION = "Sun Microsystems Inc. 1.6.0_13-11.3-b02";
038  private static final String JETTY_VERSION = "6.1.14";
039  private static final String JERSEY_VERSION = "1.1.0-ea";
040  private static final String VERSION = "4.0.0-alpha-1-SNAPSHOT";
041  private static final String REVISION = "5085d27ab17d857118a96ae3f37c00b60c925471";
042
043  public TestVersionModel() throws Exception {
044    super(VersionModel.class);
045    AS_XML = "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" standalone=\"yes\"?><Version JVM=\"Sun "
046      + "Microsystems Inc. 1.6.0_13-11.3-b02\" Jersey=\"1.1.0-ea\" "
047      + "OS=\"Linux 2.6.18-128.1.6.el5.centos.plusxen amd64\" REST=\"0.0.1\" Server=\"6.1.14\" "
048      + "Version=\"4.0.0-alpha-1-SNAPSHOT\" "
049      + "Revision=\"5085d27ab17d857118a96ae3f37c00b60c925471\"/>";
050
051    AS_PB = "CgUwLjAuMRInU3VuIE1pY3Jvc3lzdGVtcyBJbmMuIDEuNi4wXzEzLTExLjMtYjAyGi1MaW51eCAyLjYuMTg"
052      + "tMTI4LjEuNi5lbDUuY2VudG9zLnBsdXN4ZW4gYW1kNjQiBjYuMS4xNCoIMS4xLjAtZWEyFjQuMC4wLWFscGhhLT"
053      + "EtU05BUFNIT1Q6KDUwODVkMjdhYjE3ZDg1NzExOGE5NmFlM2YzN2MwMGI2MGM5MjU0NzE=";
054
055    AS_JSON = "{\"JVM\":\"Sun Microsystems Inc. 1.6.0_13-11.3-b02\",\"Jersey\":\"1.1.0-ea\","
056      + "\"OS\":\"Linux 2.6.18-128.1.6.el5.centos.plusxen amd64\",\""
057      + "REST\":\"0.0.1\",\"Server\":\"6.1.14\", \"Version\":\"4.0.0-alpha-1-SNAPSHOT\","
058      + "\"Revision\":\"5085d27ab17d857118a96ae3f37c00b60c925471\"}";
059  }
060
061  @Override
062  protected VersionModel buildTestModel() {
063    VersionModel model = new VersionModel();
064    model.setRESTVersion(REST_VERSION);
065    model.setOSVersion(OS_VERSION);
066    model.setJVMVersion(JVM_VERSION);
067    model.setServerVersion(JETTY_VERSION);
068    model.setJerseyVersion(JERSEY_VERSION);
069    model.setVersion(VERSION);
070    model.setRevision(REVISION);
071    return model;
072  }
073
074  @Override
075  protected void checkModel(VersionModel model) {
076    assertEquals(REST_VERSION, model.getRESTVersion());
077    assertEquals(OS_VERSION, model.getOSVersion());
078    assertEquals(JVM_VERSION, model.getJVMVersion());
079    assertEquals(JETTY_VERSION, model.getServerVersion());
080    assertEquals(JERSEY_VERSION, model.getJerseyVersion());
081    assertEquals(VERSION, model.getVersion());
082    assertEquals(REVISION, model.getRevision());
083  }
084}
